ined more than fifteen thousand medical personnel. Moreover, the introduction of military medicine shifted biomedicine out of elite, urban civilian institutions and laboratories and transformed it into an adaptive field-based practice for all. Universal care, practical medical education, and mobile medicine are all lasting legacies of this effort.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChinesezForeign countries. 0aMedicine, ChinesexHistoryy20th century. 0aMedicine, MilitaryzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  aBlood Bank.  aChinese American History.  aChinese Red Cross.  aGlobal Health.  aHistory of Medicine.  aMilitary Medicine.  aModern China.  aPostwar Taiwan.  aRobert Lim.  aWorld War II.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361401740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503614017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503614017.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020